No withdrawal shall be made for Emergency Expenditures under Category (8), unless and until the Bank is satisfied, and notified theBorrower of its satisfaction, that all of the conditions established under Section III.B.1(e) of Schedule 2 to the Loan Agreementin respect of said expenditures have been met.

No withdrawal shall be made under Category (7) until the Environmental and Social Management Framework, the Indigenous PeoplesPlanning Framework, the Labor Management Procedures and the Stakeholder Engagement Plan (as defined in the Amendment Letter) havebeen updated by the Borrower in a manner satisfactory to the Bank, adopted and re-disclosed in country and in the Bank´s website.

No withdrawals shall be made under Category (6) and Category 7 until the PMU has updated the Operational Manual in a mannersatisfactory to the Bank for the provision of COVID-19 Emergency Response Grants.

Schedule 2-Section I, A.6. The Borrower, through MAG (through the PMU), shall, not later than nine (9) months after the EffectiveDate, establish, and thereafter operate and maintain, at all times during Project implementation, a computerized management andmonitoring information system, satisfactory to the Bank, for purposes of monitoring the execution of each Beneficiary under anInvestment Subproject.

Schedule 2-Section I. A. 3. For purposes of enabling INDI to provide the required assistance under the Project, including,inter-alia, for the carrying out of strategic capacity building activities and for the provision of support for the implementationof the ESCP, as applicable, the Borrower, through MAG, shall, not later than four (4) months after the Effective Date, enter intoan agreement with INDI (the INDI Participation Agreement), all under terms and conditions acceptable to the Bank and as set forthin the Operational Manual.

Schedule 2-Section I. B. 3. The Borrower, through MAG (through the PMU), shall furnish to the Bank for its prior review andapproval the proposed Investment Subprojects in accordance with the criteria set forth in the Operational Manual and the ESCP.

Schedule 2-Section I. B.1. Upon approval of the pertinent Investment Sub-project under Part 2 of the Project and prior to thecarrying out of said Investment Sub-project, the Borrower, through MAG (through the PMU), shall enter into a sub-project agreement(the Investment Sub-project Agreement) with the pertinent Investment Sub-project Beneficiary under terms/conditions acceptable tothe Bank.

Schedule 2-Section I. B.4. The Borrower, through MAG (through the PMU), shall refrain from presenting to the Bank Loan withdrawalapplications and/or withdrawing Loan proceeds from the Designated Account under Category (2) of Section III.A of Schedule 3 of theLoan Agreement to finance any given Investment Subproject, until the Borrower, through MAG (through the PMU), has furnished to theBank, evidence, acceptable to the Bank, indicating that the auditor to carry out the audits referred to in Part 3(b)(iii) of theProject has been hired as provided in Section I.A.5 of Schedule 2 of the Loan Agreement.

The PMU shall refrain from presenting to the Bank Loan withdrawal applications and/or withdrawing Loan proceeds from the DesignatedAccount under Categories (6) and (7) to finance any given COVID-19 Emergency Assistance Plans, until the Borrower has furnished tothe Bank, acceptable evidence indicating the auditor to carry out the audits referred to in Part 3(b)(iii) of the Project.

Upon approval of the pertinent COVID-19 Emergency Assistance Plan under Part 4 of the Project, and prior to the carrying out ofsaid Emergency Assistance Plan, the Borrower (through the PMU), shall enter into an agreement (the COVID-19 Emergency ResponseAgreement) with the pertinent COVID-19 Emergency Response Recipient under terms and conditions acceptable to the Bank.
